laboratory_examinations.findings: No consolidation or pleural effusion at the lung bases. The liver enhances homogeneously. There is no extra- or intra-hepatic biliary duct dilatation. The gallbladder is normal. The spleen is unremarkable. The kidneys enhance symmetrically and excrete contrast symmetrically with no evidence of hydronephrosis or pyelonephritis. There is a 5 mm pancreatic hypodensity likely cyst with tiny septation. There are no pathologically enlarged lymph nodes in the retroperitoneum or mesentery. There is no free fluid or free air. There is no bowel obstruction. In the pelvis, there is a tubular structure in the right lower abdominal quadrant, measuring 1.4 cm, with enhancing wall, suggestive of possible pathology. There is a small amount of free fluid in the pelvis. No pathologically enlarged lymph nodes in the pelvic or inguinal area. Suggestion of septate uterus. Urinary bladder is unremarkable.
